<% content_for(:title) { "About - Hackatime" } %>

<div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
  <div class="bg-white shadow rounded-lg p-8">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">About Hackatime</h1>
    
    <div class="prose prose-indigo max-w-none">
      <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-6">
        Hackatime is a WakaTime-compatible coding time tracker built specifically for 
        <a href="https://hackclub.com/" class="text-indigo-600 hover:underline">Hack Club</a>.
      </p>
      
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">What is Hackatime?</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
        Hackatime tracks your coding activity across 75+ editors and provides detailed statistics, 
        leaderboards, and integrations with Slack. It's designed to help you understand your coding 
        habits and motivate you to code more.
      </p>
      
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Features</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-600 space-y-2 mb-4">
        <li>Track coding time automatically in your favorite editors</li>
        <li>View detailed statistics by project, language, and editor</li>
        <li>Compete on daily and weekly leaderboards</li>
        <li>Build and maintain coding streaks</li>
        <li>Integrate with Slack for status updates</li>
        <li>Connect your GitHub account to link projects to repositories</li>
      </ul>
      
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Getting Started</h2>
      <ol class="list-decimal list-inside text-gray-600 space-y-2 mb-4">
        <li>Sign in with your Slack account</li>
        <li>Get your API key from the settings page</li>
        <li>Install the WakaTime plugin for your editor</li>
        <li>Configure the plugin with Hackatime's API URL and your API key</li>
        <li>Start coding and watch your stats grow!</li>
      </ol>
      
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Open Source</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
        Hackatime is open source! You can find the source code on 
        <a href="https://github.com/hackclub/hackatime" class="text-indigo-600 hover:underline">GitHub</a>.
        Contributions are welcome!
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>